<TITLE> Back injury sidelines Ferdinand again </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, Jan 12 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Manchester United defender Rio Ferdinand will visit a specialist on Monday after he was ruled out of his side's home Premier League clash with Chelsea on Sunday because of a recurring back injury. The England international had been declared fit in the buildup to the game but manager Alex Ferguson said he had suffered a muscle spasm. "Rio trained all week without a problem but woke up this morning with another spasm so we're going to send him to another specialist tomorrow because it's becoming a problem for us," Ferguson told Sky Sports. Ferdinand has missed United's last four matches
